history.content: Definitely fine. Honestly you just need to know C and the stuff about the stack can be learned. I took 61c but literally had to relearn it since I took them a year apart. And after the first project 61c isn't even relevant.

children.subject: I think that's doable. For reference, I'm taking EE120, CS161, and CS170 this semester. I would say 61c is probably a little more work than 120, but regardless I think that's a good schedule.
thoughts on taking 61c , 161 , and 170 together. assuming i self-study over the summer so i'm not entirely clueless in the beginning of 161.

My test for students who want to take CS161 without 61C:  Read "Smashing the Stack for Fun and Profit".  If this makes sense to you, you can get away without the 61C prerequisite.  If it doesn't, take 61C first.
